subSubSection.paragraph:
The genus Stenosoma was described by Leach (1814) simultaneously in two different parts of the Brewster's Edinburgh Encyclopaedia: in the main section "Crustaceology" (p. 404), and in the Appendix which was published as an integral part of that section (pp. 429-434). Leach (1815) also re-described Stenosoma in his popular work "A tabular view of the external characters of four classes of animals, which Linne arranged under Insecta", a reference erroneously cited as the original description by many authors (e.g. Collinge 1917 ; Kussakin 1982 ;
Junoy and Castello 2003
). In neither of those publications was a type species designated.

